erve">Designed a 6-layer multi-connectivity </w:t></w:r><w:proofErr w:type="spellStart"/><w:r><w:t>IoT</w:t></w:r><w:proofErr w:type="spellEnd"/><w:r><w:t xml:space="preserve"> Gateway PCB built around an STM32MP1 System-on-Module (SOM), integrating Wi-Fi/Bluetooth, LTE, </w:t></w:r><w:proofErr w:type="spellStart"/><w:r><w:t>LoRa</w:t></w:r><w:proofErr w:type="spellEnd"/><w:r><w:t xml:space="preserve">, and GPS modules alongside power management, communication, debugging, and storage blocks. Applied controlled impedance routing, differential pair constraints, and a structured </w:t></w:r><w:proofErr w:type="spellStart"/><w:r><w:t>stackup</w:t></w:r><w:proofErr w:type="spellEnd"/><w:r><w:t xml:space="preserve"> to ensure RF and high-speed signal integrity, while optimising EMI performance through ground plane strategy and component placement. Fabrication files (</w:t></w:r><w:proofErr w:type="spellStart"/><w:r><w:t>Gerbers</w:t></w:r><w:proofErr w:type="spellEnd"/><w:r><w:t>, BOM, assembly drawings) were fully prepared and delivered for manufacturing.</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w:rsidR="003577D2" w:rsidRDefault="003577D2" w:rsidP="003577D2"><w:pPr><w:pStyle w:val="Paragraphedeliste"/></w:pPr><w:r><w:rPr><w:noProof/><w:lang w:eastAsia="en-GB"/></w:rPr><w:lastRenderedPageBreak/><w:drawing><wp:anchor distT="0" distB="0" distL="114300" distR="114300" simplePos="0" relativeHeight="251658240" behindDoc="0" locked="0" layoutInCell="1" allowOverlap="1"><wp:simplePos x="0" y="0"/><wp:positionH relativeFrom="margin"><wp:posOffset>266700</wp:posOffset></wp:positionH><wp:positionV relativeFrom="paragraph"><wp:posOffset>0</wp:posOffset></wp:positionV><wp:extent cx="5438775" cy="4305300"/><wp:effectExtent l="0" t="0" r="9525" b="0"/><wp:wrapTopAndBottom/><wp:docPr id="1" name="Image 1"/><wp:cNvGraphicFramePr><a:graphicFrameLocks xmlns:a="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/drawingml/2006/main" noChangeAspect="1"/></wp:cNvGraphicFramePr><a:graphic xmlns:a="http://schemas.openxmlformats.or